geocode_en.formatted_address: 21 Tung St, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong

result.adr_address: 21 Tung St, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 21 Tung St, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Blue Supreme

reviews.text:
Cool beer bar in Central, which focuses on Belgian styles.
They have bunch of kinds of nice brews both on trap and by bottle, you can ask staff which will satisfy your taste.
Food is good as well. Price is acceptable.
Accept credit card payment.
Amazing food. Loved the service. A nice chic location for dinner

Beers on tap were the worst I ever tried in my life. If you are into brewing - imagine drinking 2 weeks old product. Full of yeast and unsettled hops. Needs another 10 days for cold crushing. Murky substance in the glass. Ordered IPA and Pale Ale and barely could tell them apart. Paid the bill for my friends as an apology. Should I mention how much they charged for this broth? Avoid any any cost.

Reply to reply: It has nothing to do with vessel you ferment in. Keg fermented beer is wonderful when done right. Serving unfinished product just wrong ;) If I wanted to harvest the yeast you were using I could just breath on my wort and it would start very healthy fermentation in no time.
Fantastic craft beers and bar snacks in a very cool setting. Blue Supreme is a great spot to start a night, or end a hard day of rummaging through 'antiques' at the local street market

Food use to be so good when it first opened. Went to blue supreme recently and huge disappointment. Quality has gone down. Hummus was very sour and the taste was off - probably it went bad as my stomach was not feeling well till the day after.
